Issue #1: Service Won't Start
  Solution:
    1. Check logs: docker compose -f docker-compose.full.yml logs service-name
    2. Restart service: docker compose -f docker-compose.full.yml restart service-name
    3. Full rebuild: docker compose -f docker-compose.full.yml down && docker compose -f docker-compose.full.yml up -d --scale node-agent=5

Issue #2: Health Check Failures
  Solution:
    1. Test health endpoint: curl http://localhost:PORT/health
    2. Check service logs: docker compose -f docker-compose.full.yml logs service-name
    3. Verify dependencies: docker compose -f docker-compose.full.yml exec service-name ping dependency-service

Issue #3: Port Conflicts
  Solution:
    1. Find process: lsof -i :PORT
    2. Update docker-compose.full.yml port mappings
    3. Restart services: docker compose -f docker-compose.full.yml restart

Issue #4: Memory/CPU Issues
  Solution:
    1. Check resource usage: docker stats
    2. Adjust limits in docker-compose.full.yml
    3. Restart services: docker compose -f docker-compose.full.yml up -d --scale node-agent=5

Issue #5: Database Connection Errors
  Solution:
    1. Test service connectivity: docker compose -f docker-compose.full.yml exec backend curl -f http://localhost:8000/health
    2. Check connection string: docker compose -f docker-compose.full.yml exec backend env | grep -E 'MONGO|REDIS|DATABASE'
    3. Reset stack: docker compose -f docker-compose.full.yml down -v && docker compose -f docker-compose.full.yml up -d --scale node-agent=5

Debug Commands:
  Enter container: docker compose -f docker-compose.full.yml exec backend bash
  Check env vars: docker compose -f docker-compose.full.yml exec backend env | grep FL_
  Test connectivity: docker compose -f docker-compose.full.yml exec backend ping backend
  Check mounted volumes: docker compose -f docker-compose.full.yml exec backend ls -la /app
  View resource limits: docker inspect sovereignmap-fl | grep -A 20 Resources
